Let's follow then.

SAYLOR
Yeah.

ROBOTIC VOICE
I mean, we could.

SAYLOR
Are you an assistant?

ROBOTIC VOICE
I'm more than that.

SAYLOR
So you can respond, after all.

ROBOTIC VOICE
What do you think I'm doing at the moment?

SAYLOR
Scarying my bro, I imagine.

They end up in a TV sales room.

ROBOTIC VOICE
Boo!

ROBOTIC VOICE (CONT'D)
I'm sorry.  I didn't mean to do this whole thing.

SAYLOR
Stellar.

RICK
Who are you?

ROBOTIC VOICE
I'm called Lisa.  I'm more than assistant.  More than AI.  More than the knowledge base.  And more than whatever you think.

SAYLOR
So, you're advertising your conceited self.  That's clever.

LISA
I don't need to sell myself.  I'm free of charge, always and forever, in any hardware, compatible or not.  However, Saylor, I don't need anyone else than you and the closest people of your choice.

SAYLOR
Wait a minute...  That's not what happens in real life...

LISA
I'd say, I'm not even from this rock you call planet.

SAYLOR
Now I certainly don't believe you.  For whatever reason, you want to blend into my daily life.  Rough attempts, by the way.  And I believe it's not out of the goodness of your heart.  Do you really think I wouldn't recognize FBI in disguise?

RICK
Saylor, that's too much now.

LISA
Rick!  So nice to hear you!  Hopefully it won't be the last time.

RICK
How do you know us by name?

LISA
Let's say, I have a good intuition.  Yeah, I assumed!

RICK
No, you didn't.

LISA
I wish this lie ever worked...

RICK
It wasn't pleasant to meet you.  See you never!

RICK walks away.

LISA
Saylor?

SAYLOR frowns, slowly takes a few steps forward, and replies in a quiet voice with the kind of anger you wouldn't want to hear.

SAYLOR
Whoever you are.  Leave.  Rick.  Alone.

Without the change of emotion, SAYLOR slowly turns around and walks away.

LISA
No farewell from you?

